c-access-workflow, §WF-forge-workflow-drivers).\nforge/DEVELOPING.md:101:  [--keep-tests-without-dynamic-access] \\\nforge/DEVELOPING.md:126:- `--keep-tests-without-dynamic-access` keeps generated tests for dynamic-access workflows even if no dynamic-access call sites are covered.\nforge/DEVELOPING.md:386:coordinates, active dynamic-access classes, source-context paths, and Gradle\nforge/DEVELOPING.md:421:The `dynamic_access_iterative` workflow improves metadata accuracy by using the `generateDynamicAccessCoverageReport` Gradle task to identify which dynamic-access call sites (reflection, JNI, resources, serialization) are not yet covered by the generated tests. Instead of generating tests blindly, the workflow iterates class-by-class, sending the agent targeted prompts with the exact uncovered call sites for each class. After each attempt, the report is regenerated and coverage deltas are computed to decide whether to retry the same class or move on.\nforge/DEVELOPING.md:452:Composite strategies (run a primary workflow, then refine dynamic-access coverage):\nforge/DEVELOPING.md:459:#### Running a dynamic-access strategy\nforge/DEVELOPING.md:482:see `docs/workflows/dynamic-access.md`.\nforge/git_scripts/make_pr_new_library_support.py:37:from utility_scripts.dynamic_access_report import DynamicAccessCallSite, load_dynamic_access_coverage_report\nforge/git_scripts/make_pr_new_library_support.py:61:class DynamicAccessMetadataEvidence:\nforge/git_scripts/make_pr_new_library_support.py:67:    \"\"\"Return the total covered dynamic-access call count from library stats.\"\"\"\nforge/git_scripts/make_pr_new_library_support.py:75:    covered_calls = dynamic_access.get(\"coveredCalls\")\nforge/git_scripts/make_pr_new_library_support.py:84:        evidence: DynamicAccessMetadataEvidence | None = None,\nforge/git_scripts/make_pr_new_library_support.py:86:    \"\"\"Explain large dynamic-access/metadata-entry count differences in generated PR bodies.\"\"\"\nforge/git_scripts/make_pr_new_library_support.py:97:        \"### Metadata/dynamic-access evidence\",\nforge/git_scripts/make_pr_new_library_support.py:99:        f\"- Covered dynamic-access calls: {covered_calls}\",\nforge/git_scripts/make_pr_new_library_support.py:101:        \"- These counts are different dimensions: covered dynamic-access calls count observed call sites, \"\nforge/git_scripts/make_pr_new_library_support.py:113:        \"- Use the call-site and metadata-rule lists together to review whether the observed dynamic-access \"\nforge/git_scripts/make_pr_new_library_support.py:119:def load_dynamic_access_metadata_evidence(repo_path: str, coordinates: str) -> DynamicAccessMetadataEvidence | None:\nforge/git_scripts/make_pr_new_library_support.py:120:    \"\"\"Load covered dynamic-access call sites and generated metadata rules for PR evidence.\"\"\"\nforge/git_scripts/make_pr_new_library_support.py:131:        \"dynamic-access\",\nforge/git_scripts/make_pr_new_library_support.py:132:        \"dynamic-access-coverage.json\",\nforge/git_scripts/make_pr_new_library_support.py:147:    return DynamicAccessMetadataEvidence(\nforge/git_scripts/make_pr_new_library_support.py:166:def _format_dynamic_access_call_site(call_site: DynamicAccessCallSite) -> str:\nforge/git_scripts/make_pr_new_library_support.py:279:        dynamic_access_evidence: DynamicAccessMetadataEvidence | None = None,\nforge/git_scripts/make_pr_new_library_support.py:283:    Chunked dynamic-access parts use ``Refs`` until the final part may close the\nforge/git_scripts/make_pr_new_library_support.py:284:    backing issue (§WF-chunked-dynamic-access-pr-linking), following the chunked\nforge/git_scripts/make_pr_new_library_support.py:645:    base branch (§WF-dynamic-access-exhaust-report).\nforge/utility_scripts/issue_requested_metadata.py:27:        \"- Treat the reporter-requested metadata as mandatory even when it is unrelated to the current dynamic-access target.\",\nforge/git_scripts/common_git.py:762:    \"\"\"Re